A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Leisa Powers; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Leisa Powers; and
4 WHEREAS, Leisa Powers was a dedicated community leader who worked tirelessly to
5 support and uplift those around her, leaving a lasting impact on the City of Decatur and
6 playing an integral role in the Decatur Education Foundation; and
7 WHEREAS, since the foundation's inception, she worked alongside her husband, Tony, a
8 founding board member, to ensure its success and growth, helping to create opportunities for
9 children in Decatur to thrive; and
10 WHEREAS, in addition to her community involvement, she enjoyed a distinguished
11 professional career at Cox Enterprises as a senior manager in HR and benefit systems, where
12 she was known for her knowledge, leadership, and ability to create a supportive workplace
13 where employees could thrive; and
