14 WHEREAS, a proud and loyal resident of Georgia, she was a loving wife to her husband and
15 a devoted mother to their two wonderful children, raising her family in Decatur and
16 remaining deeply involved in the well-being of her community; and
17 WHEREAS, she gave inspiration to many through her high ideals, morals, and deep concern
18 for her fellow citizens, and the devotion, patience, and understanding she demonstrated to
19 her family and friends were admired by others; and
20 WHEREAS, she was a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation
21 for integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness, and by the example she made of her life,
22 she made this world a better place in which to live; and
23 WHEREAS, a compassionate and generous woman, Leisa Powers will long be remembered
24 for her love of family, friendship, and community and will be missed by all who had the
25 great fortune of knowing her.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 join in honoring the life and memory of Leisa Powers and express their deepest and most
28 sincere regret at her passing.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the family of Leisa
31 Powers.
